      <statement><p>Starting from <m>(y+2)^2 = \frac{1}{2}e^{x^2} + C\text{,}</m> which of the following is the correct explicit solution?</p>
<p><ul form="buttons" name="AnSwEr0001">
<li>
<p><m>y = \pm\sqrt{\frac{1}{2}e^{x^2} + C} - 2</m></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>y = \sqrt{\frac{1}{2}e^{x^2} + C} - 2</m></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>y = \pm\sqrt{\frac{1}{2}e^{x^2} + C} + 2</m></p>
