      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\text{Choice 1}</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <solution><p>Taking the square root of both sides of <m>(y+2)^2 = \frac{1}{2}e^{x^2} + C\text{:}</m></p>
<p><me>y + 2 = \pm\sqrt{\frac{1}{2}e^{x^2} + C}.</me></p>
<p>Subtracting 2 from both sides:</p>
<p><me>y = \pm\sqrt{\frac{1}{2}e^{x^2} + C} - 2.</me></p>
</solution>
